<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,715,1639]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[199,352,1435,1460]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1435,1460]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Java, Borneo (
<collectingCountry box="[525,627,1436,1460]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sarawak</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[648,762,1436,1460]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
. In his description Muir specifies Buitenzorg (now Bogor), Java (on palm tree) as 
<typeStatus box="[409,457,1472,1496]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">type</typeStatus>
locality. The locality records seem to indicate that this species is widely distributed in southern Asia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1436,715,1639]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
